# TRNspot

A modular Python package for transcriptional regulatory network (TRN) analysis using single-cell RNA-seq data. Integrates Scanpy, CellOracle, and Hotspot into a checkpoint-enabled pipeline.

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/trnspot.git
cd trnspot
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

## Quick Start

```bash
# Run full pipeline
python run_pipeline.py --input data/pbmc3k_raw.h5ad --output results/

# Run specific steps
python run_pipeline.py --steps preprocessing clustering

# Custom parameters
python run_pipeline.py --cluster-key leiden --species human --resolution 1.0

# Resume from checkpoints
python run_pipeline.py --resume
```

## Package Structure

```
trnspot/
├── core/           # Data types and utilities
├── preprocessing/  # QC, normalization, clustering, embedding
├── computation/    # CellOracle GRN and Hotspot analysis
├── pipeline/       # Pipeline orchestration and checkpoints
├── plotting/       # Plot generation utilities
├── reporting/      # HTML/PDF report generation
└── config.py       # Central configuration
```

## Usage

### Configuration

```python
from trnspot import set_random_seed, config

set_random_seed(42)
config.print_config()
config.update_config(QC_MIN_GENES=300, PLOT_DPI=600)
```

### Preprocessing

```python
from trnspot.preprocessing import perform_qc, normalize_and_transform, cluster_cells
import scanpy as sc

adata = sc.read_h5ad('data.h5ad')
adata, qc_result = perform_qc(adata)
adata, norm_result = normalize_and_transform(adata)
adata, cluster_result = cluster_cells(adata)
```

### GRN Analysis

```python
from trnspot.computation import run_celloracle_analysis, run_hotspot_analysis

# CellOracle GRN inference
adata, grn_result = run_celloracle_analysis(adata, cluster_key='leiden', species='human')

# Hotspot module analysis
adata, hotspot_result = run_hotspot_analysis(adata)
```

### Pipeline API

```python
from trnspot.pipeline import PipelineRunner, PipelineConfig

config = PipelineConfig(output_dir='results/', use_checkpoints=True)
runner = PipelineRunner(config)
result = runner.run(adata, steps=['preprocessing', 'clustering', 'celloracle'])
```

## Output Structure

```
results/
├── preprocessed_adata.h5ad
├── report.html
├── logs/
│   └── pipeline.log
├── figures/
│   ├── qc/
│   ├── grn/
│   └── hotspot/
├── celloracle/
│   └── grn_scores.csv
└── hotspot/
    └── gene_modules.csv
```

## Testing

```bash
pytest tests/ -v
pytest tests/ --cov=trnspot --cov-report=html
```

